Package: OLStrajr
Title: Ordinary Least Squares Trajectory Analysis
Version: 0.0.0.9000
Authors@R: 
    person("First", "Last", , "first.last@example.com", role = c("aut", "cre"),
           comment = c(ORCID = "YOUR-ORCID-ID"))
Description: This package provides functions for the implementation of case-by-case 
    ordinary least squares (OLS) regression and OLS trajectory analysis as detailed in 
    Carrig, Wirth, & Curran (2004) <doi:10.1207/S15328007SEM1101_9> and Rogosa & Saner (1995) <doi:10.3102/10769986020002149>. The 'cbc_lm' function offers unbiased 
    estimators of the mean population intercept and slope by calculating the mean values 
    of the OLS intercepts and slopes for each case, providing standard errors across 
    bootstrap replicates and calculating 95% confidence intervals using the empirical 
    distributions from the resampling. The 'OLStraj' function facilitates the estimation 
    of individual growth curves over time using OLS regression, providing options for 
    group-level and individual-level plots, and accommodating linear and quadratic models.
